////////////////////////////////////////////
// Translation macro for FELIX hex output //
//                                        //
// Written by Austin Schmier              //
// for sPHENIX MVTX testing purposes      //
// aschmier@vols.utk.edu                  //
////////////////////////////////////////////



Usage:
./runEventDump.sh inputfile sensor outputfile

Example:
./runEventDump.sh "rawData/test0065-210810-114740-1.dat" "2" "out.txt"

Use a raw data file as input.
Please feel free to email me with any questions or issues.


Disclaimer:
This is still not a "polished" version. I'm working on the following:
1. Including a make file instead of running with a bash script
2. Running with Valgrind to check for memory issues
3. Streamlining string-related translation methods
4. Making the "wordHandler" and "readMSD" functions their own macros
   so they can be run externally

Please feel free to send an email with any recommendations
